Link to "EU-U.S. DPF Statement and Policy"
EU-U.S. DPF Statement and Policy
This EU-U.S. DPF Statement and Policy (this “policy”) explains the rights and policies concerning Fonticons, Inc.’s (“we,” “our,” or the “company’s”)
      collection, use, sale, and sharing of the personal information relating to any user (“you”) of our website, products, services, and other online tools
      and resources. We may update and make changes to this policy, so we encourage you to review it periodically. This policy only addresses specific matters
      concerning collection, use, sale, and sharing of certain personal information. The terms herein supplement and amend our other policies, including but
      not necessarily limited to any of our other privacy policies. For additional information regarding how the company addresses privacy matters, please
      review all of our posted policies. It is the intention of our policy to ensure compliance with EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework, the UK Extension to the
      EU-U.S. DPF, and the Swiss-U.S. Data Privacy Framework, and to safeguard the rights created and outlined therein as such rights relate to citizens of
      the EU, UK, and Switzerland.
Personal Data We Collect About You.
We collect information to provide goods and/or services to you, to help improve your customer experience,
        and to support our business functions. We may collect the following categories of consumer personal data:
Identifiers:
Information that identifies, relates to, describes, or is capable of being associated with, a particular individual such as
          your name and email address.
Commercial information:
Purchase and transaction history, as well as information necessary to detect and prevent fraud when processing
          payments.
Quantitative Site Use:
Information pertaining to your use of our site, such as page views, the source of your visit, views of content
          during a visit, bandwidth utilized, stored video preferences, and information provided by you regarding your profile.
Geolocation data.
Why We Use Your Personal Information.
We use your consumer personal information for the following business purposes:
Maintaining or servicing accounts, providing customer service, processing or fulfilling orders and transactions, verifying customer information,
          processing payments, providing financing, providing analytic services, providing storage, or providing similar services;
Advertising or marketing;
Helping to ensure security and integrity and prevent fraud;
Undertaking activities to verify or maintain the quality or safety of our services or devices and to improve, upgrade, or enhance them;
Auditing or monitoring of transactions and engagements;
Compliance with our legal and regulatory obligations;
Conducting research and analysis;
To conduct other activities for legitimate business purposes
Third Parties.
The information described herein may be stored on servers owned by third parties in the ordinary course of business.
Our Participation in the EU-U.S. DPF.
In order to comply with certain domestic and international legal requirements, we participate in the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework (the "EU-U.S.
          DPF"). If you would like additional information regarding the EU-U.S. DPF other than what is contained in our Privacy Policy, such information is
          available at
https://www.dataprivacyframework.gov/
As described herein, Fonticons, Inc., a Delaware corporation, with offices in the State of Arkansas and State of Missouri, collects certain personal
          information (described above) and shares it with certain other parties (described above). As part of our participation in EU-U.S. DPF, we adhere to
          certain Principles, as described on and defined by the EU-U.S. DPF website (the "Principles"). Any of our subsidiaries also adhere to such
          Principles.
It is the intention of this policy to ensure compliance with EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework, the UK Extension to the EU-U.S. DPF, and the Swiss-U.S.
          Data Privacy Framework, and to safeguard the rights created and outlined therein as such rights relate to citizens of the EU, UK, and Switzerland.
Fonticons, Inc. complies with the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework (EU-U.S. DPF) and the UK Extension to the EU-U.S. DPF, and the Swiss-U.S. Data
          Privacy Framework (Swiss-U.S. DPF) as set forth by the U.S. Department of Commerce. Fonticons, Inc. has certified to the U.S. Department of Commerce
          that it adheres to the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework Principles (EU-U.S. DPF Principles) with regard to the processing of personal data received
          from the European Union and the United Kingdom in reliance on the EU-U.S. DPF and the UK Extension to the EU-U.S. DPF. Fonticons, Inc. has certified
          to the U.S. Department of Commerce that it adheres to the Swiss-U.S. Data Privacy Framework Principles (Swiss-U.S. DPF Principles) with regard to
          the processing of personal data received from Switzerland in reliance on the Swiss-U.S. DPF. If there is any conflict between the terms in this
          privacy policy and the EU-U.S. DPF Principles and/or the Swiss-U.S. DPF Principles, the Principles shall govern. To learn more about the Data
          Privacy Framework (DPF) Program, and to view our certification, please visit
https://www.dataprivacyframework.gov/
As described herein, Fonticons, Inc., a Delaware corporation, with offices in the State of Arkansas and State of Missouri, collects certain personal
          information (described above) and shares it with certain other parties (described above). As part of our participation in EU-U.S. DPF, we adhere to
          certain Principles, as described on and defined by the EU-U.S. DPF website (the “Principles”). Any of our subsidiaries also adhere to such
          Principles.
We are committed to applying the Principles to all data we receive from the EU in reliance on the EU-U.S. DPF.
The purposes for which we collect certain personal data is described above.
If you need to contact us, regarding inquiries, or complaints, you can reach us by email at
dpo@awesome.me
or
privacy@fontawesome.com
, or by clicking Help on
          any page at
https://fontawesome.com
". In addition, certain EU officials and organizations may be able to
          respond to your inquiries or complaints. You may find their contact information at
https://edps.europa.eu/about-edps/contact_en
or
https://edpb.europa.eu/about-edpb/more-about-edpb/contact-us_en
As described herein, the information we retain may be stored on servers owned by third parties.
You have a right to access the data that we collect about you. If you would like to do so, please contact us via the methods listed above.
Certain personal data, your email for example, is required for the use of our services. Therefore, if you do not wish for us to collect or store any
          of your personal data, then we will be unable to provide services to you.
An independent dispute resolution body is available to address complaints and provide recourse free of charge to you concerning the issues set forth
          herein. Specifically, we have elected the JAMS Data Privacy Framework for disputes relating to EU-U.S. DPF. If you need to open a dispute resolution
          matter relating to EU-U.S. DPF, information is available here:
https://www.jamsadr.com/DPF-Dispute-Resolution
Our services, including the activities described herein, may be subject to the investigatory and enforcement powers of the FTC.
By utilizing our services, you agree that, except as described herein and subject to the limitations of the laws of relevant jurisdictions, all
          matters relating to EU-U.S. DPF shall be subject to binding arbitration. You may initiate binding arbitration in the event that any dispute
          resolution procedures described by paragraph 4(xi) herein are unsuccessful. Information regarding initiating binding arbitration is available here:
https://www.dataprivacyframework.gov/framework-article/ANNEX-I-introduction
In the event we receive a lawful request by a public or legal authority, such as a subpoena, we are required to abide by such requests and may be
          required to disclose data containing your personal information, even if you would prefer that we do not make such disclosure. Such disclosures may
          be required to be made in situations including, but not limited to, the necessity to meet national security or law enforcement requirements.
The rights and obligations contained in this Privacy Policy shall inure to the benefit or our, and your, heirs, successors, and assigns.
Opting Out.
You have the opportunity to choose to opt out of your personal information (i) being disclosed to a third party or (ii) being
        used for a purpose that is materially different from the purpose(s) for which it was originally collected or subsequently authorized by the
        individuals. To exercise such option, you can reach us by email at
dpo@awesome.me
or
privacy@fontawesome.com
, or by clicking Help on any page at
https://fontawesome.com
". For your reference, we do not gather personal information specifying medical or
        health conditions, racial or ethnic origin, political opinions, religious or philosophical beliefs, trade union membership or information specifying
        the sex life of any individual
Our Liability.
The Recourse, Enforcement and Liability Principle of the Principles explains that, if we wrongfully transfer your data, we
        have continuing responsibility for the processing of such personal information. In such case, we remain liable under the Principles if our agent
        processes your personal information in a manner inconsistent with the Principles, unless we prove that we were not responsible for the event giving
        rise to the damage.
More Information.
For more information concerning the Principles, please see
https://www.dataprivacyframework.gov/program-articles/FAQs
